      <p>During the winter months, emergency beds are available for rough sleepers.</p>
      <p>To access a bed, people should visit the Homeless Day Service  between 8.30am and 12.30pm (9.00am - 12 noon at weekends), where bed spaces are allocated.</p>
      <p>If someone is unable to get to the Homeless Day Service, they should contact:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://goo.gl/maps/yyBppm7ZzK42">Housing Options, First Floor, Civic Offices, Guildhall Square, Portsmouth, PO1 2AX</a></li>
        <li>telephone: <a href="tel:023 9283 4989">023 9283 4989</a></li>
      </ul>
      <p>This service is provided by Society of St James and Salvation Army, in partnership with Portsmouth City Council.</p>
